latestIgtvVideos.title: *Live with Farah Sanjana and Neeta Lulla
#SavingtheArtist
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
‘’Giving is the Greatest Act of Grace’’
Every garment created has so many inputs from so many unseen faces and hands, that give voice to the imagination and creative output of a designer.
It is the  quiet symbiotic collaboration with our artisans, karigars, tailors, pattern cutters, and embroiderers that eventually bring to life the beautiful creations that give aesthetic meaning and pleasure to our senses.
The sad plight of this vast section of skilled but unrepresented workforce, made us deeply conscious of the need to help them, on as large a scale as we possibly could.
As caring citizens we have sincerely put our mind, energies and heart into trying to actively help  this vast section of skilled but unrepresented workforce, in this time of dire need. We are hopeful of getting a good response from everyone which  will directly benefit them. 
#SavingTheArtist campaign speaks of the following: * 80% of every purchase made will be reaching our artists linked to each of our organisations directly. This will help create a trusted channel of direct fund transfers with no middle man involved. * 20% of each sale will be shared with NGO SNEHA @snehamumbai_official a non profit organisation, to support their fight against domestic violence(a much needed effort in todays times of enforced lockdown) which will also help run their one-stop centre.

Our Fashion Family in order of appearance : 
1.Neeta Lulla @houseofneetalulla 
2.Farah Sanjana @farahsanjana 
3.Shriya Som @shriyasom
